<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-02-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-02-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="290" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d290">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Lord Lyons</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State.</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-02-26"><hi rend="italic">February</hi> 26, 1864.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Lord:</hi> I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of yesterday, and its accompaniments, relative to
                            the case of Mr. James McHugh, a prisoner at Fort Lafayette, and to
                            inform you that a copy of the papers has been communicated to Major
                            General John A. Dix, at New York.</p>
                        <p>In compliance with your request, the original certificate which
                            accompanied your note is herewith returned.</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to be, with high consideration, your lordship’s obedient
                            servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed> WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p> Right Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Lord Lyons</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>